      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Shape / spacing (2D-informed)\n- The **cationic N** is connected through a **short flexible chain** to **one aryl ring**, and via a **benzylic methylene** to the **second aryl ring**: effectively a **\u201ccationic center flanked by two aromatics\u201d** arrangement.\n- Overall resembles a **diphenylalkylamine-like pharmacophore** (common among hERG binders), though one aryl has a polar sulfonamide that may attenuate binding.",
      "tool_name": null,
