      "step_index": 3,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Structural alerts (hERG-relevant)\n- **Basic amine + two aryl/hydrophobes**: classic hERG risk motif.\n- Not exactly \u201cterfenadine-like\u201d (terfenadine is bulkier and more lipophilic with a tertiary alcohol), and **no piperidine**, but the **core pattern** (cationic center with aromatic flanks and flexible ethers) is still a known hERG-binding architecture.",
      "tool_name": null,
