      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (how it would block hERG)\nhERG blockers typically bind in the **inner vestibule** of the channel when it is open/inactivated. Mechanistically:\n- The **protonated amine** can provide a **strong electrostatic anchor** in the pore environment.\n- The **aryl rings** can occupy hydrophobic pockets and make stabilizing **\u03c0/hydrophobic contacts** with aromatic residues lining the cavity.\n- The molecule\u2019s **flexible linkers** help it adopt a conformation where the cationic center and hydrophobes align with the channel\u2019s binding determinants.",
