      "content": "## 5) VERIFICATION / UNCERTAINTY CHECK\n- **No contradiction** with the main hERG pharmacophore: it clearly has a **cationic center** and **two aryl groups** at plausible distances with flexibility.\n- **Main uncertainty:** the **sulfonamide** may reduce effective binding by lowering lipophilicity and increasing desolvation cost; this could shift it from \u201cstrong blocker\u201d to \u201cweak/moderate\u201d or, in some cases, below practical concern depending on exposure.\n- **Alternative explanation:** if the sulfonamide drives a conformation that keeps one aryl/polar region solvated and prevents deep cavity occupancy, blockade could be weaker than expected from 2D features alone.",
